    <h1>Gluten-Free Cranberry Orange Shortbread Cookies: A Delightful Treat for Everyone</h1>

    <p>Shortbread cookies are a classic treat that many of us grew up enjoying. Their buttery, crumbly texture and subtle sweetness make them a favorite for tea time, holiday gatherings, or just a simple snack. But what if you could elevate this classic cookie with a burst of citrusy orange and tart cranberries, all while keeping it gluten-free? That’s exactly what we’re diving into today with our recipe for Gluten-Free Cranberry Orange Shortbread Cookies.</p>

    <h2>Why Gluten-Free Shortbread?</h2>

    <p>Gluten-free baking has become increasingly popular, not just for those with celiac disease or gluten sensitivity, but also for people looking to explore alternative flours and healthier baking options. Traditional shortbread cookies are made with wheat flour, which contains gluten. However, with the right combination of gluten-free flours, you can achieve the same tender, melt-in-your-mouth texture without compromising on taste.</p>

    <p>In this recipe, we’ll be using a blend of almond flour and rice flour to create a gluten-free base that’s both nutritious and delicious. Almond flour adds a rich, nutty flavor and a soft texture, while rice flour helps to bind the dough and give it that classic shortbread crunch.</p>

    <h2>Ingredients You’ll Need</h2>

    <p>Before we get into the step-by-step instructions, let’s take a look at the ingredients you’ll need to make these delightful cookies:</p>

    <table>
